paragraphs.title: Load Data
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

##########################################################
#
#   Load Sales Data
#
##########################################################

lkq_sales1 = spark.read.load("/sales1.txt", "csv", delimiter="\t", inferSchema=False, header=True)

lkq_sales1 = lkq_sales1.select("Sales_Order_SID", "Location_Code", "Sold_to_Cust_Code", "Sold_To_Bus_name", "Product_Code", "Quantity", "Extended_Price", "Profit", "Margin_Pct", "Written_By_ID", "Order_Date") \
    .withColumn("Quantity", lkq_sales1["Quantity"].cast(FloatType()))               \
    .withColumn("Extended_Price", lkq_sales1["Extended_Price"].cast(FloatType()))   \
    .withColumn("Profit", lkq_sales1["Profit"].cast(FloatType()))                   \
    .withColumn("Margin_Pct", lkq_sales1["Margin_Pct"].cast(FloatType())) 

#lkq_sales1.show(10,False)
#print '\n' + str(lkq_sales1.count()) + ' total records\n'
#for i in lkq_sales1.dtypes: print str(i)

##########################################################
#
#   Load Product Data
#
##########################################################

lkq_products = spark.read.load("/products.txt", "csv", delimiter="\t", inferSchema=True, header=False)
lkq_products = lkq_products.selectExpr("_c0 as product_code", "_c1 as product_desc", "_c2 as product_line", "_c3 as product_line_desc", "_c4 as major_group", "_c5 as major_group_desc") \
    .select("product_code", "product_desc", "product_line_desc", "major_group_desc")

#for i in lkq_products.dtypes: print str(i)

##########################################################
#
#   Load MDM Data
#
##########################################################
lkq_mdm = spark.read.load("/mdm.txt", "csv", delimiter="\t", inferSchema=False, header=True)
#for i in lkq_mdm.dtypes: print str(i)

lkq_mdm = lkq_mdm.select("MDM_Region_Name","MDM_District_Name","MDM_Location_Code","MDM_Location_Name","MDM_Profit_Center_Desc","MDM_Location_Type","MDM_Financial_Status")
#for i in lkq_mdm.dtypes: print str(i)

##########################################################
#
#   Load Data into SQL
#
##########################################################
lkq_sales1.createOrReplaceTempView('lkq_sales1_sql')
lkq_products.createOrReplaceTempView('lkq_products_sql')
lkq_mdm.createOrReplaceTempView('lkq_mdm_sql')

paragraphs.title: What businesses are buying?
paragraphs.text:
%sql

SELECT sold_to_bus_name, 
    sum(extended_price) as total_revenue,
    sum(profit) as total_profit,
    sum(quantity) as total_quantity
    FROM lkq_sales1_sql
    GROUP BY sold_to_bus_name
    ORDER BY total_revenue DESC
    LIMIT 5

paragraphs.title: What are my top selling product lines?
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select product_line_desc, 
    sum(extended_price) as total_revenue,
    sum(profit) as total_profit,
    sum(quantity) as total_quantity
    from join2_sql
    where trim(product_line_desc) = "RECON ALUMINUM WHEELS" OR  
        trim(product_line_desc) = "CLASSIC PARTS" OR
        trim(product_line_desc) = "LAMPS" OR
        trim(product_line_desc) = "SHEET METAL CRASH PARTS" OR
        trim(product_line_desc) = "AIR CONDITIONING"
    group by product_line_desc
    order by total_revenue desc
    limit 500

paragraphs.title: Model Prep
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

# String Indexer
strindexer = StringIndexer(inputCol="major_group_desc", outputCol="major_group_desc_index")
modelprep1 = strindexer.fit(join2).transform(join2)

strindexer = StringIndexer(inputCol="MDM_Region_Name", outputCol="MDM_Region_Name_index")
modelprep1 = strindexer.fit(modelprep1).transform(modelprep1)


label_var    = "Extended_Price"
feature_vars = ["Quantity", "major_group_desc_index", "MDM_Region_Name_index"]


# Generate Features Vector and Label
va = VectorAssembler(inputCols=feature_vars, outputCol="features")

# Added code to drop nulls / NAs
#modelprep1.count()
modelprep1 = modelprep1.na.drop()
#modelprep1.count()

lkq_sales1_prep1 = va.transform(modelprep1).withColumn("label", col(label_var))

#lkq_sales1_prep1.show()

paragraphs.title: Split TRAINING and TESTING dataframes
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

# Random Spliting
training, testing = lkq_sales1_prep1.randomSplit([0.8, 0.2])

#lkq_sales1_prep1.count()
print "Number of records (training): " + str(training.count()) + "\n"
print "Number of records (testing):  " + str(testing.count()) + "\n"

gbt = GBTRegressor(featuresCol="features", labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", maxDepth=5, maxBins=32, maxIter=20, seed=12345)

# Make predictions.
predictions = gbtmodel.transform(testing)

# Make predictions.
predictions = glrmodel.transform(testing)

predictions.createOrReplaceTempView('predictions2_sql')
